1 Section 2902. A. The Oklahoma Department of Commerce Human
2 Services shall be responsible for the disbursement and
3 implementation of the Energy Conservation Assistance Fund.
4 B. The Department shall involve senior citizen groups, social
5 service agencies and other civic groups in publicizing such program.
6 C. The Department of Human Services, in cooperation with the
7 Oklahoma Department of Commerce, shall determine eligibility
8 requirements necessary to qualify a homeowner to obtain such grants.
9 Upon meeting any such eligibility standards, the Department of Human
10 Services shall certify to the Oklahoma Department of Commerce that
11 such homeowner is qualified to receive such grant upon notification
12 of such certification. The Oklahoma Department of Commerce Human
13 Services shall distribute the grant funds. Priorities shall be
14 established for applications according to those indicating the
15 greatest need. Low-income elderly and handicapped applicants shall
16 be given first priority.
17 D. In order to qualify for grant assistance, the property shall
18 meet all of the following requirements:
19 1. The property shall be the homestead of the applicant; and
20 2. The property for which the grant is issued shall not be
21 income-producing or used in any method other than as the principal
22 residence of the applicant.
23 E. Grants may be issued to finance the following types of
24 weatherization:
HB2115 HFLR Page 2
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 1. Structural repairs necessary to improve efficient heating
2 and cooling of the residence;
3 2. Insulation for attics, walls and water heaters;
4 3. Replacement of broken glass, inefficient doors and door
5 thresholds;
6 4. Storm windows;
7 5. Caulking and weather stripping; and
8 6. Other appropriate energy conservation measures as determined
9 by the Oklahoma Department of Commerce Human Services.
10 No grants shall be made through this program unless an energy
11 audit has been performed on the applicant's principal residence.
12 No grant shall exceed Three Thousand Dollars ($3,000.00). No
13 grant shall be awarded to any applicant with an annual income in
14 excess of the amount specified in this subsection.
15 Income eligibility shall be determined based on one hundred
16 twenty-five percent (125%) of the poverty guidelines issued by the
17 United States Office of Management and Budget.
18 F. The application for the grant shall be in such form as
19 determined by the Oklahoma Department of Commerce Human Services.
20 No grant shall be issued to any person until such person has been
21 certified as eligible by the Department of Human Services. The
22 applicant shall be provided with copies of all documents related to
23 the issuance of the grant. The applicant shall provide documents,
24 as required, concerning the status of property and household income.
