1 Section 5030. A. There is hereby created in the State Treasury
2 a revolving fund to be designated as the "Weatherization Revolving
3 Fund", which shall consist of all monies appropriated or transferred
4 to the fund. Said revolving fund shall be a continuing fund not
5 subject to fiscal year limitations and shall be under the
6 administration of the Oklahoma Department of Commerce Human Services
7 and may be disbursed without legislative appropriation. Warrants
8 for expenditures from said revolving fund shall be drawn by the
9 State Treasurer, based on claims signed by an authorized employee or
10 employees of the Oklahoma Department of Commerce Human Services and
11 approved for payment by the Director of the Office of Management and
12 Enterprise Services. It is hereby declared that energy conservation
13 is in the interest of the State of Oklahoma. The purpose of this
14 fund is to provide monies to be used for the purpose of weatherizing
15 households in Oklahoma thereby conserving the oil and natural gas
16 resources of the state.
17 B. On July 1, 1986, any unallotted cash balance in the
18 Weatherization Revolving Fund created in Section 1537.1 of this
19 title shall be transferred to the Weatherization Revolving Fund
20 created in this section. All outstanding financial obligations and
21 encumbrances of the Weatherization Revolving Fund created in Section
22 1537.1 of this title are hereby transferred to the Oklahoma
23 Department of Commerce. After November 15, 1986, any unexpended
24 balance in the Weatherization Revolving Fund created in Section
